Nabil Shaath described the talks in a joint press conference with
Fischer as "important." Germany is one of the two major donor
countries in Palestinian reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians can never give up their sovereignty over
Jerusalem and there can be no solution to the Middle East issue
without the holy city because it is a major part of Palestinian
territories occupied by Israel in 1967, and the future capital of a
Palestinian state, Shaath stressed.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Fischer said he held a "constructive and serious
dialog" with Arafat on the peace process. There is an opportunity
to push forward the peace process and reach a permanent peace
agreement between the Palestinians and Israelis, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We in the European Union as well as in Germany support the
peace process," Fischer said.
</P>
<P>
On the expected German role in the regional peace process,
Fischer said his country was not only a donor country and a source
of financial support but also an influential power in the European
Union.
</P>
<P>
The German minister arrived in the region Sunday evening on a
working visit to Israel and the Palestinian self-rule areas. He is
scheduled to meet Israeli cabinet members Monday evening. 
