said this is an "important and main issue" pertaining to Arab joint
action. An Arab League five-member committee, consisting of Egypt,
Oman, Syria, Tunisia and Yemen, will begin discussions in Cairo on
Tuesday of a mechanism for holding summit on a regular basis, he
added.
</P>
<P>
On the Iraqi issue, Moussa said Iraq should be given the hope to
see the light at the end of the tunnel. "Everyone is concerned
about the fate of the Iraqi people," he added.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has been under international sanctions since its 1990
invasion of Kuwait. Baghdad maintains that it has honored the
relevant U.N. Security Council resolutions, and calls for the
lifting of the sanctions. 
