<HEADLINE> Greece to Shorten Mandatory Military Service Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Greece will shorten its mandatory
military service by six months in the coming three years.
</P>
<P>
Greek Defense Minister Akis Tsohatzopoulos had unveiled a new
program that would gradually be completed in three years and be
combined with the hiring of 15,000 professional soldiers, the
Macedonian Press Agency (MPA) reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
As of 2001, the length of service would be reduced to 16
months from the present 18 months for the Greek army, 18 months
for the air force (presently 20 months) and 19 months for the navy
(presently 21 months). 
