the chief of UNMOVIC, which replaces the U.N. Special Commission
for Disarmament in Iraq (UNSCOM).
</P>
<P>
So far, Iraq has refused to accept UNMOVIC and U.N. Resolution
1284 adopted in December, which promises suspension of sanctions
if Iraq agrees to cooperate with UNMOVIC. 
