<HEADLINE> UK Service Industries Growth Slows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The growth in UK service industries
slowed slightly last month, but prices charged to customers hit
new highs, according to a new report.
</P>
<P>
Figures from the Chartered Institute of Purchasing and Supply
show that while the growth of business activity slowed in May, the
sector as a whole was still in a healthy condition.
</P>
<P>
The figures show employment levels were also slower than in
April, but incoming new business and prices grew faster in May
than in April.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, companies were suffering from rising
costs as skills shortages resulted in higher salaries.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that both higher costs and prices may cause some
concern for the Bank of England when it meets this week because
they could spark higher inflation.
</P>
