's protocol department Vladimir Shevchenko.
</P>
<P>
The meeting at Yeltsin's Gorki-9 residence in Moscow lasted for
about 40 minutes. Yeltsin and Clinton discussed international
issues,among them the Anti-Ballistic Missile (ABM) treaty signed
in 1972.They assured that the missile defense consultations would
go on, said Shevchenko.
</P>
