<HEADLINE> Clinton Calls for New Nature of Russian-American Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Visiting U.S. President Bill Clinton
on Monday in a speech to the Russian parliament urged to establish
a Russian-American relationship of a new nature.
</P>
<P>
Russia has passed the phase of its dependence on external aid
and now it needs foreign investments, he said at the Russian State
Duma,the lower house of the parliament.
</P>
<P>
The question America should ask is what it can do together with
Russia in the common interests, he noted. The Americans should
stop thinking that they have the answers to all questions and all
of the problems in Russia will cease to exist as soon as it sides
with the American points of view, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Russia will choose a policy that complies with its interests to
be shared by the people in a democratic way, Clinton said.
</P>
<P>
Another problem is that the majority of Russians suspect
America of not wishing good to their country, but that is not so,
he said. The Americans are interested in a strong Russia that
would be capable of upholding its territorial integrity and
development, he said. 
