<HEADLINE> Schroeder Begins Visit to Three Baltic States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BERLIN, June 5 (Xinhua) -- German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder
left Berlin for Tallinn, the capital of Estonia, to make official
visits to the three Baltic states - Estonia, Latvia and Lithuania.
It is the first visit of German Chancellor to the three Baltic
states.
</P>
<P>
Schroeder's predecessor Helmut Kohl reportedly had refused the
visit because of fear of offending Russia. But German President
Johannes Rau and his predecessor Roman Herzog had already made
visit to the three states.
</P>
<P>
During Schroeder's visit in the three states he will talk with
the leaders of the three states about the planned enlargement of
the European Union (EU)and the expansion of the North Atlantic
Treaty Organization (NATO). The three Baltic states want to join
in the two organizations.
</P>
<P>
Germany plays an important role in the two organizations and
keeps the historical influence in the Baltic region. Now Germany
is the biggest trade partner of Latvia and Lithuania, at same time
the fourth largest one of Estonia. Many German businessmen
accompany Schroeder to visit the three states. All sides hope to
boost the economic and trade relations between Germany and the
three Baltic states. 
</P>
