<DOCNO> XIE20000605.0072 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Construction of Sewer Network Underway in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Construction work of new sewer
collecting systems began here today.
</P>
<P>
With a price tag of 700 million yuan (84 million US dollars)
the project will channel sewage discharged from the bustling
financial center of the Pudong New District in the city, which is
now famous for its dazzling skyscrapers.
</P>
<P>
The 30-km underground artery pipe can collect 360,000 tons of
waste water daily.
</P>
<P>
And another 6.6-km pipeline will collect 80,000 tons of waster
water from the western part of the city.
</P>
<P>
The project is a part of the second-phase sewage disposal
program in Shanghai, which will have a total investment of 6.3
billion yuan (759 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The pipeline in the Pudong section will connect with a 130-km
long pipe, which was laid at the end of last year, running from
two industrial parks in the southwest and southern parts of the
city to a sewer treatment plant in Pudong.
</P>
<P>
All the sewage is piped to a disposal plant built at the mouth
of Yangtze River, which has a daily handling capacity of 1.7
million tons.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
