<HEADLINE> Vajpayee Calls For Conservation of Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Planting a sapling in Manali city of north India's Himachal
Pradesh state to observe World Environment Day Monday, Vajpayee
said adequate steps are needed to protect the environment from
destruction caused by unplanned development that did not take into
account long-term impact.
</P>
<P>
"In our country, the increasing stress on natural resources is
reflected in the form of polluted air, contaminated water, health
problems, diminishing forests and extinction of numerous species
of flora and fauna," said Vajpayee in a message to the nation. "It
is also reflected in the form of drought and floods."
</P>
<P>
He said environment and ecological conservation have to be the
common thread linking national policies, plans and programs,
adding that his government is committed to ensuring sustainable
development and improving quality of life of people through proper
environmental and natural resource management.
</P>
<P>
"But government alone cannot accomplish the task," he noted. "
We need the active participation and cooperation of individuals,
community organizations, voluntary groups and industry."
</P>
<P>
Also on Monday, the central government of India announced at a
World Environment Day function in New Delhi that it had decided to
hike by 15 to 25 percent funds for soil and water conservation
measures in new afforestation projects in the desert and drought-
prone areas, the PTI reported.
</P>
<P>
It said that the government is also planning to set up an
Environment Protection Fund for creating mass awareness. 
