<HEADLINE> Putin Arrives in Rome </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Vladimir Putin
arrived here Monday afternoon at the start of a two-day visit to
Italy.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Putin, who has just concluded talks with U.S.
President Bill Clinton in Moscow, is likely to discuss with
Italian Premier Giuliano Amato the issues of U.S. plans for an
anti-missile defense system, conditions in the Balkans and
Chechnya and bilateral economic and industrial agreements.
</P>
<P>
Italy, because of its geographic position, is greatly concerned
about missile programs pursued by some countries for the
development of medium and long range missiles which could
represent a threat to the national security of others.
</P>
<P>
Amato said earlier that arms issues would be one of the items
on the agenda for talks with Putin.
</P>
<P>
On his two-day visit, Putin will also meet Italian President
Carlo Azeglio Ciampi and travel to the Vatican for an audience
with Pope John Paul II.
</P>
<P>
After a visit to London in mid-April for talks with British
Prime Minister Tony Blair, Putin's visit here will mark his first
official trip abroad since his inauguration on May 7.
</P>
<P>
Putin will continue on to Spain and Germany after his visit to
Italy. 
</P>
