<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1530 GMT, June 5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA-- A great earthquake, capable of causing massive damage,
struck Sunday off the Indonesian island of Sumatra, according to
an AP report.
</P>
<P>
The quake was measured at magnitude 7.9 and occurred at 11:28 p.
m. local time, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The shock was felt strongly at Benjkulu, 70 miles north-
northeast of the epicenter, where it could have caused major
structural damages. It also was felt as far away as Jakarta, the
capital, 335 miles north-northwest of the center. (Indonesia-
Earthquake)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- France is opposed to introducing more German votes
than French votes in European Union (EU) councils of ministers in
the process of reforming the EU institutions, French Delegate
Minister for European Affairs Pierre Moscovici said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the radio and television channel Europe 1,
Moscovici said that France and Germany are close to a bilateral
agreement on EU institutional reform, "but we have not agreed that
France have fewer votes in the European councils than Germany,
because France is also a great country."
</P>
<P>
Germany asks for more votes in the councils because its
population is much greater than that of France. (France-Germany-EU)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
