<HEADLINE> Cambodia Ratifies Extradition Treaty With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia's National Assembly on
Monday ratified an extradition treaty with China in joint efforts
to fight against all forms of crimes and strengthen law
enforcement between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
It is the second treaty Cambodia has officially ratified since
becoming a full member of the Association of Southeast Asian
nations (ASEAN). The first such kind of treaty was ratified last
year with Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Most immigrants are coming to Cambodia for transit and buy
travel documents before traveling to another country, mostly to
the United States, Australia and Europe, police said.
</P>
<P>
The treaty stresses the importance of bilateral cooperation in
preventing all forms of crimes. 
