<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Share prices ended sharply higher
on the Singapore Stock Market Monday boosted by a rally on Wall
Street at the end of last week.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) shot up 72.03 points to
close at 1,982.43 in active trading.
</P>
<P>
The total volume increased to 492.56 million shares valued at 1.
032 billion Singapore dollars (about 599.98 million U.S. dollars).
Gainers overwhelmed losers by 328 to 40 with 174 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
SPHAsiaOne topped the actives chart as it registered a turnover
of 34.12 million shares. It was followed by MediaRing which had 33.
81 million units done. GMG was the next with 22.96 million
counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Venture was the biggest gainer of the day with a hefty gain of
240 cents to close at 20.5 Singapore dollars. DBS surged up 160
cents to finish at 21.1 Singapore dollars. Creative 50 moved up
150 cents to close at 46.9 Singapore dollars.
