<HEADLINE> Fund for Rhino Conservation Launched in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The Malaysian Rhino Trust Fund
(MRTF) was launched Monday with the main objective of generating
income for rhinoceros conservation efforts in the country.
</P>
<P>
The fund, launched by the Pacific Asia Tourism Association(PATA)
Malaysia Chapter, will also serve as an awareness campaign to the
public, officials said at the launch held in the northwestern
state of Pulau Pinang, according to Bernama news agency.
</P>
<P>
The amount of the fund was however not announced.
</P>
<P>
The public, especially schoolchildren, are taught the
importance of nature and the rhinoceros is used as the flagship
species to emphasize the importance of the ecosystem, said Hadi
Mohamad, veterinary officer of the Rhino Conservation Center (RCC)
which will be used as a living classroom for the students to have
hands-on experience on what they have learned.
</P>
<P>
The center uses the "gene-pool" concept whereby the animals
were released into their natural habitat to allow them to breed on
their own.
</P>
<P>
The 4,160-hactare center currently manages two male and five
female rhinoceroses captured in threatened areas throughout
peninsular Malaysia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
