<HEADLINE> Engineering Specialists Urged to Contribute to Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Specialists in the engineering
circle are today urged to make greater contributions to China's
economy by providing professional consultation services to
decision makers and enterprise managers.
</P>
<P>
Song Jian, president of the Chinese Academy of Engineering (CAE)
, said the CAE has decided to set up a special committee to boost
links among research institutes, enterprises and industrial
departments, and to help enterprises enhance innovation capability.
</P>
<P>
"China cannot become an economic giant without overwhelming
strength in its engineering technology and manufacturing," Song
said at the fifth conference of CAE academicians, which began here
today.
</P>
<P>
As a leading consultative body, the 544-academician CAE is now
focusing on providing consultative services to major policy makers
and project heads.
</P>
<P>
The academicians have made contributions over the past two
years in many fields, such as development of high-speed trains,
aero industry, agriculture, pharmaceuticals, and metallurgy, Song
said.
</P>
<P>
Some of them were invited to help some large state-owned
enterprises re-structure their development strategy while
conducting technological innovation, and that will be continued in
the future, he noted. 
