<HEADLINE> Ugandan Army Officers Required to Declare Wealth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Senior officers in Ugandan army
have been required to declare their wealth under a new law, Army
Spokesman Shaban Bantariza disclosed in a telephone interview with
Xinhua Monday.
</P>
<P>
High-ranking officers of the Uganda People's Defence Forces
(UPDF) will be demanded to declare the amount of wealth they have
and how they got it, including those of their wives' and
children's, Bantariza said.
</P>
<P>
"The law is necessary to be implemented," he said, referring to
that quite a few army top officers were widely believed very rich.
</P>
<P>
Some officers have declared their wealth so far, according to
the spokesman. But many others have remained silent.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Chief of Military Intelligence Noble Mayombo has backed
the Leadership Code, saying that the UPDF High Command should
declare their property to the Inspector General of Government in
line with the code.
</P>
<P>
He said that they are passing through this legislations so that
it could be implemented. 
</P>
</TEXT>
