<HEADLINE> China Builds National Science Think Tank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Sciences (
CAS), home to top scientists in China, is going all out to make
itself a national science think tank.
</P>
<P>
"The CAS is working hard to make itself the top academic
assessment body and the most influential consultation organ for
decision-making in China, and will realize the goal of becoming
the country's science think tank," president of CAS Lu Yongxiang
said at the tenth conference of CAS academicians, which began here
today.
</P>
<P>
Lu said that CAS will continue to provide strategic
consultations for the central government on some key issues, such
as developing the western region, enhancing military force through
science and technology, and helping state-owned enterprises
sharpen their competitive edges through technological renovation.
</P>
<P>
"History has repeatedly demonstrated that scientific and
technological groups are needed to join the consultation and
decision of lots of strategic and foresighted issues concerning
the country's development," Lu stressed.
</P>
<P>
CAS has presented many group reports on hot issues since the
program of building a national science think tank was initiated
two years ago.
</P>
<P>
The academicians' opinions on the western region development,
sustainable development of agriculture, and prevention of sand
storms have been taken into serious consideration by the nation's
high-ranking officials, Lu said.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1949, CAS is comprised of 625-member academic
committees and some 120 institutes throughout the country. It has
become China's reigning sci-tech consultative body and research
center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
