<HEADLINE> China Issues Daily Air Quality Reports of 42 Key Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- China today issued its first daily
report on the quality of air in 42 of its major cities and ended
the three years' publication of such reports on a weekly basis.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, Taiyuan in northern China's Shanxi
Province is the only city that suffered slight air pollution today,
while Beijing, Shijiazhuang, Jinan, Yantai, Guiyang, Xi'an,
Lanzhou and Xining had extremely slight air pollution.
</P>
<P>
The report, issued by the China Environmental Monitoring Center,
said that Tianjin, Hohhot, Shenyang, Shanghai, Nanjing, Suzhou,
Hangzhou, Fuzhou, Guangzhou, Wuhan, Lhasa and 16 other cities
enjoyed fairly good air.
</P>
<P>
Excellent air was reported in Nanchang, Shenzhen, Zhuhai,
Haikou, Kunming and Yinchuan, it said.
</P>
<P>
Taiyuan, Beijing, Tianjin, Xi'an, Shanghai and 28 other cities
listed suspended particles as the major pollutants, while sulfur
dioxide was the major pollutant in Guiyang, Nanning and Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
The 42 cities include China's four municipalities directly
under the central government, the provincial and regional capitals
and 10 key coastal cities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
