<HEADLINE> HK Stocks Close Sharply Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks closed sharply
higher Monday on signs that the U.S. economy is slowing down,
reassuring that the need for further local interest rate rises was
fading.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Hang Seng Index gained a mammoth 577.58 points,
or 3.78 percent, to close at 15,891.68, bringing the total rise in
the past two trading days to 920.49 points.
</P>
<P>
Turnover totaled 14.658 billion HK dollars (1.879 billion U.S.
dollars), up 2.059 billion HK dollars (264 million U.S. dollars)
from Friday's 12.599 billion HK dollars (1.615 billion U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices of Hang Seng Index, Finance, Properties
and Commerce and Industry registered big gains, rising by 3.38
percent, 4.95 percent and 4.16 percent, respectively while
Utilities lost 1.15 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index and the Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corp. Index gained 0.37 percent and 2.11 percent,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng IT Index rose 4.69 percent to close at 3,087.85
and the Hang Seng IT Portfolio Index 3.21 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong stocks went up 359.69 points, or 2.35 percent, to
open at 15,643.79 Monday and closed the morning session at 15,864.
91. 
