<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Soeharto Undergoes Investigation Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Former Indonesian President
Soeharto underwent investigation again at his residence here
Monday for corruption charges.
</P>
<P>
"Today's investigation still focused on the foundations he
chaired, particularly in connection with the distribution of the
foundations' fund," Spokesman of the Attorney General Office (AGO)
Yushar Yahya told reporters after the questioning.
</P>
<P>
He said prosecutors from the AGO filed 25 questions during the
two and half hours of questioning.
</P>
<P>
But no reports were available on the health condition of the 78-
years old man at the time of the investigation.
</P>
<P>
A member of Soeharto's lawyer team Mohammad Assegaf said
Soeharto's health condition "is not conducive enough for
investigation."
</P>
<P>
Last Monday, the AGO prosecutors ceased the investigation when
Soeharto's blood pressure rose up to 170/80 mm hg after he
answered 24 long and complicated questions.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto has been under house arrest since last Monday.
</P>
<P>
He is suspected of abusing power and authority during his 32
years of rule.
</P>
<P>
Attorney General Marzuki Darusman has said dossiers of Soeharto
's case will be submitted to the court in August. 
</P>
</TEXT>
