<HEADLINE> Rain Delays French Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The start of play at the French Open
was delayed on Monday because of rain showers, according to
reports.
</P>
<P>
Two women's doubles matches had been scheduled to start play
on Centre Court and Court Suzanne Lenglen at 0900 GMT to be
followed by the remaining men's fourth round matches.
</P>
<P>
Russian 12th seed Marat Safin was taking on French sixth seed
Cedric Pioline later on Centre Court to be followed by Australian
ninth seed Lleyton Hewitt against Spain's Albert Costa.
</P>
<P>
Court Suzanne Lenglen is due host third-seeded Swede Magnus
Norman's match against last year's runner-up Andrei Medvedev and
Argentine Franco Squillari against Moroccan 15th seed Younes El
Aynaoui.
</P>
<P>
However, French weather forecasters said they were expecting
showers throughout the day.  
</P>
