<HEADLINE> Inge de Bruijn Breaks World Record in 50-meter Freestyle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Inge de Bruijn of the Netherlands
set a new world record in the women's 50-meter freestyle at the
Dutch national championships, reports from Amsterdam said on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
De Bruijn swam the 50-meter freestyle in 24.48 seconds on
Sunday, broke her own mark by 0.3 seconds from the title she
shared with China's Le Jingyi.
</P>
<P>
It was the fourth time in 10 days that De Bruijn set a new
women's world record and just a week after her previous title,
reports said. 
</P>
