<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fire Hits Squatters Site in Manila, Killing Eight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Eight people were killed in a four-
hour fire which struck a large squatters' colony near a local
government agency building Monday in Quezon City, Metro Manila.
</P>
<P>
Initial reports from the office of the local bureau of fire
protection said the fire that started Monday morning inside a
bakery near a building of the Social Security System spread
quickly, killing the eight people.
</P>
<P>
All fire stations in Metro Manila received an alarm and the
fire was put out four hours later.
</P>
<P>
The total amount of damage caused by the fire is still under
estimation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
