</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Indonesian President Abdurrahman Wahid Monday told
the newly appointed International Monetary Fund (IMF) managing
director Horst Koehler that the government will not introduce any
form of capital controls.
</P>
<P>
"The president said that there is no logic if Indonesia
introduce capital control," Koehler told reporters after meeting
Wahid here Monday morning. Koehler arrived here Sunday on the
latest leg of an Asian tour. His visit to Jakarta was made after
the IMF approved on Friday a 372 million U.S. dollar loan to help
Indonesia finance its key economic reform program. (Indonesia-IMF
Chief)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
