leader George Speight and his men an ultimatum to release their
hostages and lay down their guns, the Australian Associated Press
(AAP) reported.
</P>
<P>
The AAP said that in the army's strongest warning yet to the
rebel leader, military government head and army Commander Frank
Bainimarama said: "We will not entertain any more demands by
George Speight and his men." Bainimarama was quoted as saying in a
statement that talks to try to free 31 government hostages held by
Speight at gunpoint since May 19 had reached deadlock. (Fiji-
Military-Ultimatum) 
