<HEADLINE> Weekly Highlights of Trade-Related News (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of major trade-related
news released by Xinhua last week (May 29 - June 4) are as follows:
</P>
<P>
 Foreign Trade
</P>
<P>
-- China's foreign trade has been growing on a fast track in
the first four months this year with trade volume totaling 137.1
billion U.S. dollars, up 38.8 percent year on year.
</P>
<P>
-- Customs in Zhuhai City in south China's Guangdong province
recently seized 140 smuggled second-hand cars worth more than four
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
-- China's motorcycle exports will increase to 500,000 units
this year. The exports will mainly target Africa, South America
and Southeast Asia, according to official from the State
Administration of Machine-Building Industry.
</P>
