<BODY>
<HEADLINE> May Inflation Up 4.1 Percent in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The year-on-year-inflation in the
Philippines in May rose to 4.1 percent compared with April's 3.7
percent, the government said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The rise in inflation in May is due to higher prices of food,
beverage and tobacco as well as services, the National Statistics
Office NSO) said in a report.
</P>
<P>
The inflation figure, which brought the January-May average to
3.3 percent, fell in line with market expectations when compared
to the same month last year, the NSO said.
</P>
<P>
The May inflation figure was a significant improvement from the
6.6 percent registered in the same month in 1999, the government
agency added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000605.0236 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Parliament Begins Discussion on Budget </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The first budget session of the
parliament in the new millennium began Monday amid a boycott by
main opposition political parties.
</P>
<P>
The national budget for the fiscal year 2000-2001 will be
presented by Finance Minister Shah A.M.S. Kibria on June 8. In
July, 18 treasury bills and 23 private members' bills will be
placed in the parliament.
</P>
<P>
The parliament will sit on 36 working days, making it the
longest budget session of the seventh parliament during the Awami
League government.
</P>
<P>
Members of the main opposition parties, the Bangladesh
Nationalist Party (BNP), the Jatiya Party and the Jamaat-e-Islami,
have been boycotting the parliament for about a year, and the long
budget session may strip some members of parliament (MPs) of
membership.
</P>
<P>
The country's constitution says an MP would vacate his seat for
absence from parliament, without leave of the parliament, for 90
consecutive sitting days.
</P>
<P>
According to parliament sources, some 15 MPs, including
opposition leader Begum Khaleda Zia and Jatiya Party chief Ershad,
are heading toward the red mark of 90 days' absence that may strip
them of their parliament membership.
</P>
<P>
Once the opposition leaders are stripped of the membership,
another political crisis may be triggered in the country,
observers here said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000605.0237 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pacers Refuse To Be Sacrificial Lamb To Lakers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The NBA final series begins Wednesday in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
"We can fine-tune a lot of things that we can do better in
order to become NBA champions," said the Pacers point guard Galen
Rose, the team's scoring leader in the regular season who is
second to Reggie Miller (23.8) in the playoffs with a 20.1 average.
</P>
<P>
For all but two of the Pacers this is the first trip to the NBA
Finals. Reserves Sam Perkins and Zan Tabak are the exceptions and
Tabak was a member of the 1995 Houston Rockets championship team.
</P>
<P>
"The Lakers are certainly a powerful, talented team. Whatever
happens, we've got to be healthy and play our game. We've got to
go out and play relaxed," said Perkins, who has the most playoff
experience of any Pacer with 158 games.
</P>
<P>
"The games in the NBA Finals can be a once in a lifetime
experience." he added.
</P>
<P>
The Pacers reached the NBA Finals by beating the New York
Knicks, the team that eliminated the Pacers twice in their
previous four trips to the conference
finals, in Game 6 on Friday.
</P>
<P>
However, the Pacers center Rik Smits who is averaging 11.3
points and 3.4 rebounds in this year's playoffs, was anticipating
a tough matchup against the Lakers center Shaquille O'Neal.
</P>
<P>
"You've got to try and keep him away from the basket, try to
limit his touches," Smits said of the 7-1, 315-pound O'Neal.
</P>
<P>
The Lakers center took league-leading playoff averages of 28.8
points and 15.4 rebounds into Sunday night's game. The league's
MVP led the NBA with a 29.7 point average and a .574 percentage
from the field during the regular season.
</P>
<P>
A key player for the Pacers in the NBA Finals will be Dale
Davis, the team's rebounding leader.
</P>
<P>
"With Shaq it is going to be tough to get rebounds. He's big,
he's strong and he's effective under the basket," Davis said. "Now
there's a hungry feeling for us. We're right there, and now we
have to have a little faith."
</P>
<P>
The Lakers finally earned a berth in the NBA Finals Sunday
evening by rallying for an 89-84 victory over the Portland Trail
Blazers in Game 7 of the Western Conference finals.
</P>
<P>
The Lakers, on the verge of losing three straight games for the
first time all season, scored 15 consecutive points in the fourth
quarter to erase a 15-point Blazers lead.
</P>
<P>
O'Neal, rendered ineffective most of the game by Blazers'
double- and triple-teaming defense, scored nine points in the
fourth quarter, punctuating the rally with a thundering dunk on a
lob pass from Kobe Bryant that put the Lakers ahead 85-79 with 40
seconds to play.
</P>
<P>
The usually unemotional O'Neal waved his index fingers at the
crowd with an amazed expression on his face as he ran downcourt.
</P>
<P>
O'Neal had 18 points and nine rebounds and was 8-of-12 from the
free throws line, including two that tied the game 77-77 with 2:44
to play.
</P>
<P>
Bryant, the other half of the superstar tandem that is supposed
to lead this franchise back to its historic greatness, had 25
points and 11 rebounds. Bryant, who made just six of 12 free
throws in the game, made two to put Los Angeles ahead for good, 81-
79 with 1:34 remaining.
</P>
<P>
Rasheed Wallace scored 30 points on 13-for-26 shooting but had
six of the Blazers' 13 consecutive misses during the Lakers' run
that wiped out a 75-60 lead. Wallace also missed two free throws
with Blazers trailing 81-79 with 1:25 to go.
</P>
<P>
Scottie Pippen, brought to Portland to provide the leadership
the team needed to win a championship, fouled out with 25 seconds
to go with 12 points and 10 rebounds. He was just 3-of-10 from the
field.
</P>
<P>
The Blazers, who had beaten the Lakers twice in Los Angeles in
the playoffs, were trying to become the seventh team to come back
from being down 3-1 to win a series and the first to do it in the
conference finals. Most of Sunday evening, they looked as if they
would.
</P>
<P>
The Lakers and the Pacers will fight for the first NBA champion
in the new millennium. The Game 1 will start on Wednesday in the
Staples Center in downtown Los Angeles.  
</P>
</TEXT>
