<HEADLINE> 2 killed, 3 Injured In S.Lanka's Traffic Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 5 (Xinhua) -- At least two people were killed and
three others injured Sunday evening when a train collided with a
car carrying five people at an unprotected railway crossing at
Kapuwatta in Western Province of Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
The train bound for Puttalam from Colombo reduced speed closer
to Kapuwatta but the driver of the motor car was unable to move
off from the unprotected railway crossing, eye witnesses were
quoted by the Island Sunday newspaper as saying.
</P>
<P>
The three injured were in a critical condition.
</P>
<P>
An investigation into the cause of the accident is under way,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
Unprotected railway crossings claim several hundred lives each
year in the country.
</P>
<P>
About 15 years ago, then prime minister Ranasinghe Premadasa
ordered that make-shift barriers be constructed and manned at
every unprotected railway crossing in the country.
</P>
<P>
The measure had brought the death toll down. However, before
long the make-shift barriers have again been neglected and many of
them do not function, causing such accidents to rise again.
</P>
</TEXT>
