<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Calls for Improving Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar has called on every
individual, every nation and the entire international community to
make timely endeavor to improve the quality of environment and
promote sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a ceremony here Sunday observing the Year 2000
World Environment Day which falls on Monday, Myanmar Foreign
Minister U Win Aung stressed the vital need to have a spirit of
global partnership to address the environmental problems that
confront humanity, warning that many of the problems are
transboundary in nature, the New Light of Myanmar newspaper
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
"Despite some remarkable improvements in the global system of
environmental management, the world's environment is still under
stress and there are still many outstanding challenges in the
beginning of this new millennium," he said.
</P>
<P>
Win Aung, who is also chairman of the Myanmar National
Commission for Environmental Affairs (NCEA), called for acting
right now for achieving sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
On Myanmar's environmental affairs, he said the government has
over the past decade paid increased attention to environmental
protection and initiated many important programs and projects to
protect and conserve the country's rich natural resources with
sustainable management of forests, land and mineral resources
being promoted.
</P>
<P>
In order to prevent and arrest land and forest degradation, the
government has launched special projects including the greening of
the dry zone.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the NCEA formulated the Myanmar Agenda 21 in 1997,
in which many important programs and activities for sustainable
development are outlined.
</P>
<P>
He reaffirmed that Myanmar will never disregard the eco-systems
of the country in its economic development endeavors, emphasizing
that progress must go hand-in-hand with the preservation and
protection of the country's natural conditions and resources.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar marks the World Environment Day every year with various
activities including photo, poster and essay contests to raise
public awareness of environmental issues and to promote the sense
of duty and responsibility towards caring for the environment.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
