<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Fourth seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov of
Russia survived his third five-set match of the tournament Sunday,
outclassing Fernando Vicente of Spain 5-7, 6-3, 5-7, 7-6 (7-4), 8-
6.
</P>
<P>
In Sunday's four men's singles matches totaling 12 hours, 53
minutes, the Russian has played 19 sets and 196 games.
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov will take on No. 5 Brazilian Gustavo Kuerten In the
quarter-finals on Tuesday. Kuerten earlier beat No. 11 Nicolas
Lapentti of Ecuador 6-3, 6-4, 7-6 (7-4).
