<HEADLINE> 12 Killed in Bus Crash in Bandung, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Twelve passengers were killed when
a speeding bus crashed into a pine tree at the foot of Tangkuban
Perahu volcano near Bandung, about 180 kilometers southeast of
Jakarta, on Sunday, the Jakarta Post reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The ill-fated bus, carrying 31 students, was on its way to
Bandung from the hilly tourist resort, which is 60 kilometers away.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted police as saying that the bus smashed into the
tree on the left side of the road and rolled several times before
landing upside down in a ditch.
</P>
<P>
West Java Police chief for traffic control Col. Anang Y.S. said
that he suspected the brakes of the bus had failed while it was
going downhill, judging from the 50-meter-long skid marks on the
winding road leading to the scene of the accident. 
