<HEADLINE> Conference of CAS and CAE Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,000 academicians
gathered in Beijing today at the conference of the Chinese Academy
of Sciences (CAS) and the Chinese Academy of Engineering (CAE),
focusing on China's scientific and technological development in
the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The two academies will elect the third group of foreign
academicians and decide on the winners of Chen Jiageng scientific
award and the China Engineering Prize during the conference.
</P>
<P>
Academicians will make in-depth discussions on the frontier
issues of scientific research and engineering technology and on
the development of west China, and will offer advice for the
country's policy-makers during the five-day conference.
</P>
<P>
Symposiums on scientific achievements and development trends
will also be held during the conference.
</P>
<P>
The CAS and the CAE, which were founded in 1949 and 1994
respectively, are the highest science and technology consultative
institutions and academic thinking tanks. Research findings of the
members of the two academies represent the country's top research
level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
