<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Urban Population in China Totals 376 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The urban population in China's 668
cities totals 376 million by the end of last year, according to an
official report released here today.
</P>
<P>
The report, titled "China Environmental Situation Bulletin
1999", said China's urbanization level increased to 30.9 percent,
up half a percentage point over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the population density in urban areas
reached 462 per square kilometres, with planned urban areas
totaling 812,800 square kilometres, the report said.  
