<DOCNO> XIE20000605.0279 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1stlead: Strong Earthquake Hits Bengkulu, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake measuring 7.9
on the Richter Scale hit Bengkulu on Sunday night, killing at
least 20 people and injuring scores of others, according to
reports reaching here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The first tremors hit at 23:28 p.m. (1628 GMT) on Sunday and
lasted for a few minutes, followed by several strong aftershocks.
</P>
<P>
The reports quoted the U.S. Geological Survey as saying that
the quake was centered 33 kilometers below the earth's surface in
the Indian Ocean about 110 kilometers southwest of Bengkulu on the
western Sumatran coast.
</P>
<P>
The Antara News Agency said that there was an atmosphere of
panic in Bengkulu, a city of about 1.2 million, after the quake
hit. Residents of the city had rushed from their houses and many
stayed out in the open overnight.
</P>
<P>
Several buildings in the Bengkulu city collapsed and rescuers
were searching for people buried in the rubble during the quake,
police said, adding that rescue efforts were hampered by the fact
that the local electricity supply had been knocked out.
</P>
<P>
Antara quoted meteorology officials as saying that the tremor
was felt in various towns and cities in neighboring provinces of
West Sumatra and Lampung. The quake was also felt as far away as
in Jakarta, about 640 kilometers southeast of Bengkulu.
</P>
<P>
The quake was one of the strongest recorded in recent years in
the country. In December 1992, an earthquake measuring 7 on the
Richter Scale caused a tsunami that killed about 2,500 people on
Flores island in eastern Indonesia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
