<HEADLINE> Netherlands Wins Men's Champions Trophy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Stephan Veen scored a golden goal
to give the Netherlands a 2-1 victory over Germany in the men's
Field Hockey Champions' Trophy final in Amsterdam, Netherlands, on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 1999 international player of the year broke the deadlock 11
minutes into extra time to make sure the world and Olympic
champions go to the Sydney Games as holders of all hockey's major
titles.
</P>
<P>
It was the fifth Netherlands' victory in the tournament and
their third in five years -- and avenged a defeat by Germany in
last year's European final.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands outclassed Germany 3-2 in Saturday's women's
final to set up the double success. 
