<HEADLINE> Dynamo Kiev Captures Eighth Straight Ukrainian Crown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Dynamo Kiev came from a two-goal
deficit to capture their eighth consecutive Ukrainian soccer
championship with a 3-2 win at Karpaty Lviv on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Igor Makovei and Andriy Pokladok put Karpaty 2-0 ahead just 16
minutes into the match, but Dynamo fought back with two goals from
Uzbek striker Maxim Shatskikh and another by Georgian Georgi
Demetradze.
</P>
<P>
Shatskikh pulled one back in the 20th minute and Demetradze
equalized in the 64th.
</P>
<P>
Five minutes later, Shatskikh scored the winning goal to give
Dynamo an unbeatable 15-point lead over second-placed Shakhtar
Donetsk.
</P>
<P>
Dynamo have 72 points from 26 matches while Shakhtar, 3-1
winners against Kryvbas Kryviy Rih, have 57 points from 27 games.
