<HEADLINE> Chinese Doctors Successfully Separate Siamese Twins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Doctors at a hospital in Susong
County of east China's Anhui Province successfully separated 49-
day-old siamese twins early last month.
</P>
<P>
A local woman named Xu Cuiqin gave birth in March to the twins,
who were connected at the buttocks, sacroiliac, and rectum.
</P>
<P>
The parents wanted doctors to perform the separation but couldn
't afford the expensive surgery, so the hospital decided to do the
operation free of charge.
</P>
<P>
A team of surgeons from several departments worked together to
carry out the four-hour operation.
</P>
<P>
Both babies are reported in good condition. 
