<HEADLINE> Netherlands Beats Poland 3-1 in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Netherlands defeated Poland 3-1
in a friendly soccer tournament held in Lausanne, Switzerland, on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Frank de Boer opened the scoring for the Netherlands in the
29th minute. His teammate Patrick Kluivert added two more goals in
the 56th and 61st minutes.
</P>
<P>
Poland's Pawel Kryszalowicz scored the team's lone goal in the
38th minute of the game.
</P>
<P>
About 6,000 spectators watched the match. 
