<DOCNO> XIE20000605.0329 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mandela Launches Rural Energy Delivery Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Former South African president
Nelson Mandela launched here on Monday the Shell Foundation by
introducing the new charity organization's two pilot projects to
improve energy service delivery to the rural poor.
</P>
<P>
The first project, to be run by the Energy and Development
Research Center in Cape Town, includes a monitoring and evaluation
program to support the government's off-grid rural electrification
initiative, the petroleum giant said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that the project will enhance long-term
community sustainability by providing rural residents access to
the relevant resources to build economic and social capacity.
</P>
<P>
The other program will monitor and contribute to the creation
of clean development mechanisms, which will be administered by
the South African Mineral and Energy Policy Center, the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
"One of the major issues in South Africa and the developing
world is access to energy and clean, affordable sources of power,"
Mandela said, adding that "I'm delighted that Shell will encourage
the use of sustainable energy sources." 
</P>
</TEXT>
