<HEADLINE> Fresh Fighting Breaks out Between Rwanda, Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Fresh fighting broke out Monday noon
between Rwandese and Ugandan troops in Kisangani in the war-torn
Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC), Zambia News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
According to the DRC Minister of Human Rights Leonard Okitundu,
visiting Zambian President Frederick Chiluba, who was holding
consultative talks with the DRC President Laurent Kabila in
Lubumbash, immediately condemned the action and the continued
killing of innocent people.
</P>
<P>
He said it is sad that even after the April 14 meeting in the
Ugandan capital Kampala to strengthen the Lusaka peace process,
fighting has erupted again.
</P>
<P>
It is senseless for people to continue killing each other
because there would be no people to govern if the war continued,
he said.
</P>
<P>
"The people of Congo want peace, the people of Congo deserve
peace, we can't say all is well until the fighting stops," he
added.
</P>
<P>
At the Kampala meeting, signatories including Rwanda and Uganda
agreed to withdraw their troops within a 15-kilometer radius.
</P>
