<HEADLINE> Ethiopians Make Donation for Warfront, War-displaced: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- A total sum of 244 million birr
(about 30 million U.S. dollars) has been raised in support of
Ethiopian troops at warfront and the war-displaced people, the
National Fund Soliciting Committee said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The money was raised during the period between June 11, 1998 to
June 1, 2000, the committee said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia has been at war with neighboring Eritrea over border
disputes since May 1998.
</P>
<P>
According to the committee, more than two thirds of the total
donation was raised by government departments, non-governmental
organizations, associations and individuals in the country while
the rest came from Ethiopians abroad and foreign governments.
</P>
<P>
About 42 million birr (about 5 million U.S. dollars) came from
foreign governments and Ethiopians aboard, the committee said,
adding a total of 176.1 million birr (22 million U.S. dollars) has
already been used for the warfront and the rehabilitation of war
displaced people. 
</P>
