The Dow Jones industrial average rose 20.54 at 10,815.30,
extending its gain of 502.52 points last week.
</P>
<P>
The technology heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 8.38 at 3,821.
76. The composite rose 608.27 point last week, its biggest week
gain in history.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were mixed. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500
index fell 9.63 at 1,467.63.
</P>
<P>
Investors were still in a buying mood Monday after a series of
economic data released last week showed the signs of slowdown in
the U.S. economy.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the optimism that drove stocks higher last week
remained intact because the new data would discourage the Federal
Reserve to raise interest rates aggressively following six hikes
since last June.
</P>
<P>
IBM, Advanced Micro Devices and Ariba rose, but Qualcomm and
Amazon.com fell.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index fell 4.53 at 655.16 and the American Stock
Exchange index fell 2.75 at 920.57. But The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies rose 0.27 at 513.30.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 5-to-4 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,657 down, 1,345 up and 411
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 831.27 million shares from 1.15 billion
in the previous session. 
