<HEADLINE> Fifth World Health Conference Opens in Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The Fifth World Conference of
Health Promotion began Monday in Mexico's capital with the
participation of over 60 ministers and 100 delegations of
countries members of WHO.
</P>
<P>
General Director of the World Health Organization (WHO) Gro
Harlem Brundtland said at a forum that health is a motor for
economic, social and health development of nations.
</P>
<P>
Brundtland upheld the imparting of sexual health among
adolescents in developing countries and a reducing in world
tobacco consumption, especially among women and minors.
</P>
<P>
Addiction to tobacco is responsible for annual death of 4
million people, that is, eight per second, and will go up to 10
million in 2030, said Brundtland at the first stage of the Fifth
World Conference for Health Promotion.
</P>
<P>
Regarding human immune deficiency virus (HIV) and its great
propagation in Africa, the WHO official said this problem has been
taken on by the Security Assembly of the United Nations
Organization.
</P>
<P>
This meeting, which is to end on June 9, will examine the
subjects of "Preparing the Scene, Reviewing Past Achievements and
Present Challenges," "Scientific Basis for Health Promotion" and "
Increasing Investment in Health Development." 
</P>
